  "texts": [
    "US ARPA-H recently funded Sun Vectors Inc. up to $13.4m for developing cell-free adenovirus vector manufacturing.",
    "81 China's 14th Five-Year Plan for the Bioeconomy 82, 83 highlights gene therapy as a priority research area (among many), meaning that the field is likely to receive substantial state support for infrastructure, commercialisation and workforce development, along with support to develop data assets and commercialise innovations.",
    "Some proportion of this is likely to go to non-viral vectors such as lipid nanoparticles, which are a research priority in China, but given the potential scale of state support this is still likely to influence viral vector design capabilities.",
    "2 There are some important technical barriers to scaling that will require moderate resources to overcome.",
    "The availability of suitable data is likely to be a limiting factor for the prediction of the in vivo and/or tissue-specific properties of viral vectors."
  ]
